Python Bindings for HDFS
Author: Kien Trinh
Email: kientt86@gmail.com
Date: Oct 08 2010


This is python extending module use to access HDFS.

Prerequisites:
	+ C module libhdfs installed
	+ Python module numpy installed

Install:
	+ git clone git@github.com:kientt86/libhdfs.git
	+ cd libhdfs
	+ python setup.py install
	
Using:
	>>import hdfs
	>>handle = hdfs.connect("localhost",54310)
	>>hdfs.exist(handle,"/mydata")
	>>0
	>>hdfs.write(handle,"/mydata","Hello World")
	>>11
	>>hdfs.exist(handle,"/mydata")
	>>1
	>>r = hdfs.read(handle,"/mydata")
	>>print r.data
	>>Hello World
	>>hdfs.delete(handle,"/mydata")
	>>hdfs.exist(handle,"/mydata")
	>>0
	>>hdfs.disconnect()